Name: UF in Chile - Energy Management and Engineering
About: The program is set-up as an international industrial energy consulting company doing work in Chile, in collaboration with the host: Pontificia Universidad Catolica de Valparaiso, Chile. Science and engineering students will closely work with local plant engineers, develop critical skills, and become instruments of change by evaluating the efficient use of energy in industrial processes, alternative and/or renewable energy sources, technically and economically. Students will participate in an ambitious program with site visits to local industries, with a great amount of time to get to know some relevant cultural sites and cities as are Valparaiso, Vina del Mar, Santiago, enjoy the local cuisine, local arts and crafts, and more.

Name: Aalto University School of Business
About: Aalto University is a highly ranked business university in Europe. Established in 1911, Aalto is the largest and leading business university in Finland, offering the most comprehensive range of degree programs in the field of economics and business administration. At Aalto, highly qualified scientific research merges with corporate connections, providing the students with a combination of extensive theoretical studies and real business life experiences. The University has actively adopted modern teaching methods and increased student involvement in the teaching and learning process.

Name: Aarhus BSS
About: Aarhus University is the second largest university in Denmark and Aarhus BSS is one of Europe's leading business schools, with over 13,000 students in attendance. A triple-crown accreditation (EQUIS, AMBA and AACSB) places Aarhus BSS among the best business schools worldwide and on a par with the London Business School, INSEAD in France, and the University of Washington, USA. With a population in excess of 270,000 inhabitants, Aarhus is the second largest city in Denmark. It was founded by Vikings around year 750. Today, Aarhus is known as the capital of the province, recognized for its thriving business and commercial sector as well as the many schools and educational institutions located in the area. The downtown area hosts a mixture of cobbled streets, green parks, old monuments and modern buildings in addition to the Aarhus River, which runs through the city's center.

Name: Aoyama Gakuin University
About: AGU has established a national reputation for the quality of its education and its international ambiance and is widely recognized as one of the leading private universities in Japan. Aoyama Gakuin University aims to educate students with a strong sense of social responsibility and morality in order to contribute to society and today's world in accordance with its educational policy based on the Christian faith. The university's undergraduate and graduate programs include courses on literature, law, economics, business, international politics, economics, communication, science, engineering and cultural studies. Aoyama Gakuin University has been champion of the prestigious Hakone Ekiden five times in the last six years

Name: Aston University - Business
About: Aston University was established in 1895 and has a proven record of academic excellence. The Aston Business School is one of the largest and most highly regarded business schools in Europe. Located in the bustling city of Birmingham, there are many social and cultural activities available for students to enjoy. The university embraces international culture and hosts students from over 65 countries around the world. Aston is known for its close-knit campus atmosphere, allowing for international students to feel at home during their stay.

Name: BI Norwegian Business School
About: BI Norwegian Business School, established in 1943, is the second largest academic institution in Norway and one of the largest business schools in Europe. Norway is one of the leading producers of aluminum, magnesium, Ferro-alloys and chemicals, and is a major supplier of oil and natural gas. Due to this, the society's standard of living is very high and the average GNP per capita is one of the highest in the world.

Name: Bocconi University
About: Established in 1902, Bocconi was the first university in Italy to offer a degree in economics. The University strives to meet the demands of scientific research and training in the Italian economic system. As a result, much attention is given to both economic and civic life in order to support innovation and development in businesses nationwide. As part of its mission, Bocconi has established a center of international culture based on the cultivation of relations with the leading players in world economics. Bocconi has had a long-standing tradition of hospitality toward international guests since 1974. The program continues to grow and now welcomes more than 500 exchange students from over 100 partner institutions. The cultural enrichment and diversity among students enliven the courses and allow individuals to become acquainted with different aspects of academic and social traditions. Students enjoy the cultural learning experience not only in the classroom but in the city as well. In addition to enjoying museums, theatres, shops, and cinemas, students can go dancing, listen to live music, and take advantage of numerous travel options. As one would expect, most social activities take place on Friday and Saturday nights, whereas Sunday and Monday are very subdued and many places are closed. On Wednesday evenings, young people flock to the cinema for discount ticket night. Bocconi offers many services to its exchange students each term. An on-site orientation is provided during the weeks before classes begin, and there is a “Student Exchange Network” made up of former exchange students who offer tutoring and organize events each semester. Additionally, the International Relations office provides each student with a mailbox on campus, free e-mail and computer access, two academic advisors to assist with registration, internship opportunities, and many extra-curricular activities. Students may take advantage of special tickets for performances at La Scala, weekend trips to the mountains, conferences with world-class speakers, and much more.

Name: Cardiff University
About: The University of Florida’s College of Liberal Arts and Science offers students the opportunity to study in Cardiff, Wales. Cardiff University is a public research university in Cardiff, Wales. Founded in 1883, the University is a highly regarded research institution. It is home to 2,495 undergraduate students and has over 6,000 international students attending the institution.

Name: Catolica Lisbon School of Business and Economics
About: Católica Lisbon School of Business & Economics is Portugal’s first business school and belongs to the Portuguese Catholic University, one of the leading institutions of its kind. CATÓLICA-LISBON is accredited by all three management education associations, EQUIS, AMBA and AACSB – a great accomplishment as less than 1% of all business schools worldwide can claim this triple accreditation. It is also the first and only Portuguese Business School ranked in the Financial Times Executive Education Rankings. In 2009, the institute was ranked as the 37th best business school in the world and the 17th best in Europe. The CATÓLICA-LISBON experience is made to be international. The student body represents over 30 different nationalities and 50% of the students are international students. In addition, 35% of CATÓLICA-LISBON’s faculty is from abroad.

Name: Chulalongkorn University
About: Chulalongkorn University is the oldest and one of the most prestigious universities in Thailand. Founded in 1917 by King Vajiravudh (Rama VI), the university was named as a tribute to the king’s royal father, King Chulalongkorn (Rama V). Over a period of time, Chulalongkorn University, or Chula for short, has grown to become a full-fledged university. Today, Chula has eighteen faculties, a graduate school, eleven research institutes, three teaching institutes, and four affiliated institutions with more than 2,800 faculty members. The Chulalongkorn University campus covers 500 acres in the heart of Bangkok, the capital of Thailand. The campus is within reach of the major business and financial district, as well as various other facilities.

Name: Chuo University
About: Chuo University was established in 1885. Today it is one of the largest and most prestigious private universities in Japan and is particularly renowned for accomplishments in law, policy studies, science and engineering. Many of Chuo's Business and Economics graduates have gone on to become top-level executives at major corporations in Japan and abroad. During Chuo's 134-year history, they have grown into a comprehensive university with eight faculties, seven graduate schools, and two professional graduate schools, in addition to nine research institutes, four affiliated high schools, and two affiliated junior high schools. Chuo still continues to produce many of Japan's judges, prosecutors and lawyers. Chuo was founded on the spirit of “Fostering the Ability to Apply Knowledge to Practice”, and they aspire to provide practical education that helps young people meet the demands of today’s global society.

Name: EADA Business School
About: EADA, founded in 1957, was one of the first Spanish institutions to offer executive training programmes to the business community. For more than 50 years close to 100000 participants from over 40 different countries have entrusted their training to us, a fact that highlights EADA as one of the most innovative and prestigious business schools in Spain. EADA is the only management institution in Spain with its own residential training centre. This is a vital tool in the EADA methodology as participants attend a series of professional development modules during the year where outdoor training is noted for the development of leadership and teambuilding skills. EADA has been awarded the AMBA and EQUIS accreditations, which recognise the quality of its masters and MBA programmes. Currently these accreditations are only held by 4 business schools in Spain and by a selected group of the world's most prestigious business schools. EADA is also a member of the Executive MBA Council.

Name: Eastern Switzerland University of Applied Sciences (OST)
About: OST offer studies at Bachelor’s and Master’s level in technology and planning sciences at a breathtakingly scenic campus on Lake Zurich. OST teach Bachelor and Master students in practice-oriented study programmes such as civil engineering, electrical engineering, renewable energies and environmental engineering, computer science, landscape architecture, mechanical engineering and innovation, spatial planning and industrial engineering.

Name: EBS Universität für Wirtschaft und Recht
About: The EBS University of Business and Law exchange program is open only to graduate business students. If interested, please contact Ana Portocarrero, Director of MAIB and MSM programs, at ana.portocarrero@warrington.ufl.edu.

Name: Ecole de Management de Lyon
About: The Hough Graduate School of Business  is pleased to announce the following exchange program. EM Lyon is a well-respected business school in France. It has renowned faculty and extensive company contacts. The education offered at EM Lyon is centered on entrepreneurship, innovation and humanism. Exchange students are allowed to take part in all career activities, including interviewing with companies of interest for jobs or internships. Through carefully designed courses, in-depth specializations, hands-on learning and a dedicated careers team, students will work together to develop the skills they need to become a leader in their field.

Name: Ecole d'Ingénieurs de PURPAN - French, Food & Wine (IBC Program)
About: The University of Florida’s College of Agriculture and Life Sciences offers students the opportunity to study at École d'ingénieurs de Purpan in Toulouse, France. The Ecole d’Ingénieurs de PURPAN, a Jesuit private College founded in 1919, has maintained a spirit of direct collaboration with the agricultural environment. It is administrered by a non-profit association and depends on the French Ministry of Agriculture. The campus is very pleasant and at a human scale. International Bachelor Certificate in Animal Productions & Food Sciences (IBC):  Some modules may be open to exchange students (Semester 1 : focus on Animal Productions / Semester 2 : focus on Food Science)

Name: Ecole Superieure de Commerce de Toulouse - Barcelona
About: The Barcelona business school is notable for the highly international profile of its students. More than 60% of students on the Bachelor program are international and come from over 60 different countries. For this reason, the working language on the campus is primarily English. Each year, TBS Barcelona hosts more than 700 students, 36% of whom are international, 58% French and 6% Spanish. Barcelona, the Catalan capital and the second largest city in Spain, is a dynamic European business center and one of the world’s most popular and cosmopolitan destinations. Its outstanding setting by the sea, along with its role as a center of commerce and its innovative spirit, have made it a focal point of attraction and a cultural melting pot. The Bachelor in Management is delivered at TBS Barcelona, which is also home to the official Master in Management program as well as its own degrees: MSc Fashion & Luxury Marketing, MSc Financial Management & Control, MSc Tourism & Hospitality Management, MSc International Busines, MSc Marketing Management and the Summer School.

Name: Ecole Superieure de Commerce de Toulouse - ESCT
About: This program is specifically designed for Graduate Business Students and will participate in an Exchange with Toulouse Business School in France. Today, TBS is one of France’s leading integrated management schools, with a primary mission of preparing students for managerial responsibilities through the development of their analytical, integrative, and interpersonal skills while promoting a lifelong learning process. The international scope and academic tradition at TBS continues to evolve in exciting directions, with partnerships around the world and new degree programs taught on campuses in Barcelona and Casablanca.

Name: ESCI (Pompeu Fabra)
About: ESCI – Universitat Pompeu Fabra (UPF) was created in 1993 through a joint initiative between the Government of Catalonia and Universitat Pompeu Fabra, a public university located in Barcelona. The founding objective was to prepare students for the necessary internationalization of the Catalan economic and productive fabric. At ESCI classes are small and instruction is of a high quality, emphasizing practical application. The teaching staff consists of lecturers from ESCI and from UPF’s departments of Economics and Business and Humanities amongst others; as well as renowned professionals from the world of international business. The ESCI building, designed by the architect Rafael Cáceres Zurita, reflects the message of internationalism inherent in the school’s academic activity. It is centrally located in the Barcelona city center, near Passeig de Picasso, the Cataluña Parliament and the Barcelona Zoo.

Name: Global E3 -  University of New South Wales
About: In order to provide an even extensive list of opportunities to UF engineering students, the College of Engineering has partnered with IIE/Global Engineering Education Exchange to enhance its offerings.  Programs listed under the Global E3 option are exchange programs and run at the same cost as other UF exchange programs. Global E3: is an international exchange program for engineering students at member institutions, has overseas members that include a consortium of western European universities plus selected individual institutions in other world regions, including Asia, central and eastern Europe and Latin America, provides opportunities for students to receive academic credit for courses taken at an overseas institution and practical training in a foreign setting for summer, semester or academic year, has been recognized and supported by the National Science Foundation and the US Department of Education

About: In order to provide an even extensive list of opportunities to UF engineering students, the College of Engineering has partnered with IIE/Global Engineering Education Exchange to enhance its offerings.  Programs listed under the Global E3 option are exchange programs and run at the same cost as other UF exchange programs. Name: Global E3 - Chalmers University of Technology
About: Chalmers University of Technology was founded in 1829 and named after William Chalmers, a director of the Swedish East India Company, who set aside funds in his will to establish an “industry school for poor children”. Located in Gothenburg, on the beautiful west coast of Sweden, the center for Manufacturing, Biotech and the Automotive Industry. Chalmers boasts close to 11,000 students of which about 20% are international students from over 80 countries. The University hosts 13 Departments, engaged in research, innovation, and education, mostly in engineering, science, shipping, and architecture. Chalmers is one of the most prestigious universities of technology in Europe, known for its close collaboration with industry. Chalmers utilizes modern pedagogical methods such as problem-based learning and project-based teamwork under authentic conditions. The University currently offers over 700 courses taught in English at both undergraduate- and graduate level that are broadly available for incoming exchange students. A new initiative on Campus is our Fuse learning environment, which is a modern makerspace and lab – a creative meeting place where education, research, industry, and the public sector come together to develop, test, and implement ideas. It is also the physical location for the Tracks initiative – a cutting-edge educational concept that offers students and alumni interdisciplinary courses in close collaboration with the wider community.

Global E3: is an international exchange program for engineering students at member institutions, has overseas members that include a consortium of western European universities plus selected individual institutions in other world regions, including Asia, central and eastern Europe and Latin America, provides opportunities for students to receive academic credit for courses taken at an overseas institution and practical training in a foreign setting for summer, semester or academic year, has been recognized and supported by the National Science Foundation and the US Department of Education

Name: Grenoble Ecole de Management
About: Located in the heart of the business district and next to Grenoble’s World Trade Centre, Grenoble Ecole de Management is a major player in European and international affairs. A top-ten French business school, Grenoble has designed the Undergraduate Program in International Business for students who wish to enhance their knowledge of international business, management, international culture, and foreign language. The school will provide you with an enriching learning experience in multicultural groups and in a business environment of multinational companies.

Name: Hamburg University of Applied Sciences
About: Studying abroad gives students a unique insight into the global nature of engineering. Future employers are looking for engineers who can differentiate themselves not just in terms of knowledge and skills, but also the ability to relate the knowledge in a global setting. Studying abroad gives Gator Engineers the edge to differentiate themselves in an increasingly competitive environment. It also allows for personal growth and the capability to communicate with people from all cultures. Global competency is essential for engineers from any country who now compete in an international market for engineering know-how. With over 16,000 students Hamburg University of Applied Sciences ("HAW Hamburg") is the second largest institution of higher education in the Hamburg region and one of the largest of its kind in Germany. Practice orientation is our trademark and small groups, interdisciplinary projects and academic support ensure that our students feel at home at our university. 2,000 international students study here, representing over 100 nations.

Name: HAS Green Academy
About: Are you interested in food, agriculture and horticulture, international business, sustainability, biology, plants, or animals? Then you are welcome at HAS Green Academy! HAS has over 3,000 full-time students. Their new(er) name reflects the shift they're making as a university, towards a future as a go-to center of expertise for agriculture, food, and the living environment.

Name: Hebrew University
About: Consistently ranked as one of the Top 100 universities in the world, The Hebrew University of Jerusalem offers world-class exchange programs for university and college students interested in broadening their horizons while receiving outstanding theoretical and practical instruction.

Name: Hochschule der Medien
About: Hochschule der Medien is a public university (funded by the state of Baden-Württemberg) which teaches media specialists. Since September 1st, 2001, Hochschule der Medien has brought together the combined know-how of the former Fachhochschule für Druck und Medien (HDM) – a traditional educational institution for printing- and media-technologies - and Hochschule für Bibliotheks- und Informationswesen (HBI). Hochschule der Medien covers a broad spectrum of media expertise: from printed media to electronic media, from design to business administration, from library science to advertising, from content for media to packaging technology, from computer science to information science to publishing and electronic media. About 30 accredited Bachelor’s and Master’s degree programmes mirror this diversity. At the moment, about 5500 students are enrolled at the university.

Name: Hochschule Osnabrueck - University of Applied Sciences - Business Internship
About: Hochschule Osnabrück - University of Applied Sciences was founded in 1971 and currently has over 13,000 students. In addition, more than 800 visiting students from over 85 countries study at Osnabrück every year. For UF business students, a semester at HS Osnabrück also brings an opportunity to intern at a multinational firm. Although fluency in the German language is not necessary, it is encouraged that students interested in interning enroll in a German “crash” course upon arriving at Osnabrück. Read more on the Heavener International Programs website.

Name: Hochschule Osnabrueck - University of Applied Sciences
About: Hochschule Osnabrück - University of Applied Sciences was founded in 1971 and currently has over 13,000 students. In addition, more than 800 visiting students from over 85 countries study at Osnabrück every year. For UF business students, a semester at HS Osnabrück also brings an opportunity to intern at a multinational firm. Although fluency in the German language is not necessary, it is encouraged that students interested in interning enroll in a German “crash” course upon arriving at Osnabrück. Read more on the Heavener International Programs website.

Name: IE Business School
About: IE Business School is recognized as one of the world’s top business schools by the Financial Times, The Economist, and Wall Street Journal. IE offers Masters, Doctorate and Executive Education programs. IE’s student population is culturally diverse, representing more than 80 countries. The IE campus is located in central Madrid, providing students access to everything the city has to offer: Spain’s largest financial center, the Spanish language, arts & culture, leisure and much more…

Name: Institute of Technology Bandung
About: Institut Teknologi Bandung (ITB) or Bandung Institute of Technology, was founded on March 2, 1959 by the Indonesian government as an institution of higher learning of science, technology, and fine arts, with a mission of education, research, and service to the community. ITB as an outstanding, distinguished, independent, and internationally recognized university that leads changes toward welfare improvement of the Indonesian nation and the world. ITB is ranked 313th at 2021 QS World University Rankings, and 62nd in QS Asian University Rankings.

Name: International University of Japan
About: The University is 300 km away from Tokyo, which can be reached by Shinkansen (bullet train) in about an hour and a half. Students find themselves in an atmosphere which is both typically Japanese and strongly international; this makes the experience particularly interesting.

Name: Kansai Gaidai University
About: Kansai Gaidai University is located in Hirakata, Osaka, Japan. It is a private university focusing on foreign language studies. Kansai Gaidai is known for its large Asian Studies program for international exchange students as well as for its Intensive English Studies program for Japanese students planning to study abroad.There are currently two academic campuses: the Nakamiya Campus and the Hotani Campus. Currently, there are about 15,000 students enrolled including two year and four year students from across all regions of Japan. Students from dozens of countries are also present for the majority of the year.

Name: Korea University Business School
About: Founded in 1905, Korea University Business School was the first business school established in South Korea. Because of the school’s leadership and innovation in management education, KUBS has indisputably become the most prestigious business school in the country. The teaching and research facilities at KUBS are cutting edge, and parallel the facilities found in top business schools around the world. KUBS is located in the capital city of Seoul, where students can experience Korea’s rich history and culture. Seoul is Asia’s largest and most culturally diverse city, offering the perfect environment for students to broaden their knowledge and understanding of the Korean business environment, society, and culture.

Name: Kyoto University
About: Founded in 1897, Kyoto Imperial University is second oldest university in Japan. KyotoU is consistently ranked amongst the top two in Japan, the top ten in Asia, and the world's top fifty institutions of higher education. Founded upon the principles of its motto, “freedom of academic culture”, KyotoU is currently composed of three campuses with ten Faculties, eighteen Graduate Schools, thirteen Research Institutes, and twenty-two Research and Educational Centers.

Name: Lancaster University
About: Lancaster University is a public research university in northern England with a student population of 13,600. Lancaster offers a rich curriculum with strengths in Biological Sciences, Environmental Studies, Women's Studies, English Literature, and History. It also has one of the largest business schools in Britain with a top research ranking. The university's vision for the future is to be a sustainable and academically excellent institution that is recognized as one of the leading universities in the world.

Name: Leiden University - Law
About: Leiden Law School is one of Leiden University’s seven faculties. Each year more than 1000 students choose to study Law, Notarial Law, Tax Law or Criminology. With our international focus and roots going far back in the Dutch legal order, we have trained many generations of legal professionals for key positions in a society governed by the rule of law.   Our research is not limited to one single spearhead, but we strive to conduct excellent and cutting-edge research across the full breadth of the law. We are proud of our position in international rankings, such as the Times Higher Education World University Rankings.

Name: Leiden University
About: Leiden University is the oldest university in The Netherlands, founded in 1575 by Prince William of Orange. Today, Leiden is fully accredited modern university with an enrolment of over 18,000 students, including approximately 1,600 international students. The university buildings are interspersed throughout the town itself, which makes students' residences within walking and cycling distance of the academic buildings and city shopping areas. The City of Leiden with a population of 118,000 is conveniently located in the political, cultural and economic heart of the Netherlands.  Amsterdam, Rotterdam and Utrecht are just 30 minutes away by train and The Hague and Schiphol International Airport is just a 15 minute train ride from Leiden.While the principal language of academic instruction is Dutch, the majority of students and faculty speak English and the study abroad program is constantly increasing courses offered in English, with approximately 100 or more courses in English per semester.

Name: L'Institut d'Etudes Politiques (Sciences Po) - Dijon campus
About: Study in France at an institute thought of to be one of the world's most reputable and prestigious schools of the social sciences! For over one hundred years as a leading social science institution for both teaching and research, Sciences Po has been educating the best young minds and preparing them to begin brilliant careers of leadership throughout the country and the world. SciencesPo has 6 campuses in different parts of France. Students can choose any of these campuses to complete their study. Each campus specializes in a particular region of the world! Make sure to choose the campus that fulfills your academic and professional needs!

About: Study in France at an institute thought of to be one of the world's most reputable and prestigious schools of the social sciences! SciencesPo has 6 campuses in different parts of France. Students can choose any of these campuses to complete their study. Each campus specializes in a particular region of the world! Make sure to choose the campus that fulfills your academic and professional needs!

Name: L'institut Superieur De L'aeronautique Et De L'espace (ISAE-SUPAERO)
About: ISAE SUPAERO is a school of engineering founded in 1909 and is the first in the world to specialize in aerospace engineering. It is part of the University of Toulouse.  Henri Ziegler, the main developer of the airbus program, is an alumnus.

Name: Manchester Business School - Graduate Level
About: The University of Manchester has a distinguished heritage that started back in 1824. It is the largest university in the United Kingdom, and receives more applications than any other university in the country. A new strategic vision for the university is responsible for many changes. AMBS provides world-class business and management education and is a progressive school, delivering cutting edge business thinking and teaching.

Name: Manchester Business School - Undergraduate Level
About: The University of Manchester has a distinguished heritage that started back in 1824. It is the largest university in the United Kingdom, and receives more applications than any other university in the country. A new strategic vision for the university is responsible for many changes. AMBS provides world-class business and management education and is a progressive school, delivering cutting edge business thinking and teaching. Please make sure to consult the Warrington University of Manchester Page for detailed information on the program and course availability. You can also read the Fact Sheet for more information.

Name: Monash University - Malaysia Campus
About: The University of Florida’s College of Liberal Arts and Science offers students the opportunity to study in Selangor, Malaysia Campus of Monash University. Established in 1958, Monash University quickly grew to become the largest university in Australia, with over 60,000 students. Monash is ranked in the world's top 100 universities by QS World Ranking  and a member of the prestigious Group of Eight, a coalition of Australia's largest and oldest universities that are consitently ranked highest of all Australian universities.

Name: Monash University
About: The University of Florida’s College of Liberal Arts and Science offers students the opportunity to study in Melbourne, Australia. Established in 1958, Monash University quickly grew to become the largest university in Australia, with over 60,000 students. Monash is ranked in the world's top 100 universities by QS World Ranking  and a member of the prestigious Group of Eight, a coalition of Australia's largest and oldest universities that are consitently ranked highest of all Australian universities.

Name: Nagoya University
About: The Nagoya University Program for Academic Exchange (NUPACE) offers a unique curriculum consisting of Japanese language instruction, Japan area/intercultural studies, and courses in the student’s major field of study, taught both in English and Japanese. Nagoya University offers over 800 courses taught in English and is ideal for students in International Studies, Japanese or STEM majors.

Name: Nanyang Technological University
About: Established in 1991, Nanyang Technological University, Singapore (NTU Singapore) has roots that go back to 1981 when its predecessor institution, Nanyang Technological Institute, was set up on the grounds of the former Nanyang University as a teaching university. Today, NTU is a research-intensive institution recognised globally for its impactful research, education and innovation, with strengths in many areas shaping the 4th Industrial Revolution. The NTU Smart Campus is a living test bed for Singapore’s Smart Nation initiative and a model of sustainable living.

Name: National Central University
About: National Central University is a university with long-standing traditions in Taiwan. There are 8 colleges: Earth Science, Electrical Engineering and Computer Science, Engineering, Hakka Studies, Health Science and Technology, Liberal Arts, Science, and Management. NCU is an environment-friendly green campus based on our solid foundations of sustainable development. NCU puts emphasis on holistic education, providing students with a platform for self-learning and the realization. In addition to achieving outstanding performances in their professions, students should be able to think reflexively, fit into the society maturely and considerately, and keep the down-to-earth attitude of NCU.

Name: National Chengchi University
About: Founded in 1927, National Chengchi University (NCCU) has earned a reputation as an institution of higher education celebrated for its studies in the humanities, social sciences, and management/administration sciences. Over several decades, NCCU has refined itself into nine colleges, including Commerce, Liberal Arts, Science, Social Sciences, Law, Foreign Languages, Communication, International Affairs, and Education. NCCU is home to over 15,000 students, 600 full-time professors, 70 researchers, and over 200 part-time lectures dispersed among 33 academic departments.

Name: National University of Singapore - Liberal Arts and Sciences
About: A leading global university centred in Asia, the National University of Singapore (NUS) was founded in 1905 as a modest medical college with 23 students. Today, Singapore’s flagship university spans three campuses in Kent Ridge, Bukit Timah and Outram, and is widely seen as among the best universities in Asia and the world.

Name: Newcastle University
About: The University of Florida’s College of Liberal Arts and Science offers students the opportunity to study in Newcastle upon Tyne in North East England. Newcastle University is a public research university with overseas campuses in Singapore and Malaysia. The university is a red brick university and a member of the Russell Group, an association of research-intensive UK universities. This year Newcastle ranked first in the UK and eighth in the world for sustainable development in the Times Higher Education Impact Rankings.

Name: Oslo New University College
About: Spend a semester in Oslo, Norway while learning about peace and conflict!  "Being the home of the renowned Nobel Peace Prize has also inspired vibrant discussions on issues of peace and conflict among policy makers, scholars and students. This legacy has created an academic environment with world-leading research in the fields related to International Relations and Peace and Conflict Studies." -Oslo New Univresity College This is an autumn only semester program where you will study specific course modules in English, towards Peace and Conflict Studies. Starting in 2024, there will be a few Psychology courses offered as well. The program is great for students in Political Sciences, International Studies, and European Studies.

Name: Queensland University of Technology
About: The Queensland University of Technology was founded in January 1989. Since then, the school has continued to grow and develop. QUT now has 50,000 students with 6,000 international students. The university is known as a "university for the real world" due to its connection with the industry as well as the relevant teaching. The academic staff consult in industry and work on industry projects which often involve students. The university also ranked in the top 300 universities globally in 2016.

Name: Rheinische Friedrich-Wilhelms Universität Bonn
About: The birthplace of Beethoven, Bonn, Germany is now a lively academic town and cultural center. Situated on the picturesque Rhine River, Bonn's proximity to the centers of European politics enable visitors and residents alike to witness European history unfold before their eyes. All UF students are welcome to study at the University of Bonn for a semester or full academic year. The University of Bonn is considered to be one of Europe's most important institutions of higher education. As a leading research university, it has evolved into a truly prominent international institution as well and it's alumni include five Nobel Prize winners.

Name: Royal Holloway University of London
About: The University of Florida’s College of Liberal Arts and Sciences offers students the opportunity to study in Egham, UK at Royal Holloway, University of London. Students can study during the fall, spring, or academic year. Royal Holloway, University of London, founded in 1879, is ranked in the top 30 of all UK universities. As a leading research university, it offers a broad range of subjects and has a strong tradition of academic excellence. The historic campus is considered one of the most beautiful in the world and is where most teaching and social activities take place. With a student population of just over 9000, students enjoy a close-knit community and small class sizes.

Name: Royal Melbourne Institute of Technology - Vietnam Campus
About: RMIT University Vietnam offers high-quality undergraduate and postgraduate programs that keep up to date with the latest industry trends. Our international learning environment encourages cultural awareness, critical thinking, experimentation and creativity. At RMIT, you’ll experience an education that prepares you for success, exposes you to new ideas and equips you with the skills and knowledge to excel in your chosen career.

Name: Royal Melbourne Institute of Technology
About: The Royal Melbourne Institute of Technology was founded in 1887 with a focus on the study of technology and design. The school has continued to grow and develop with the city of Melbourne.  The student population is around 70,000 students with about 30,000 international students. The university is ranked as one of the top 100 schools in Communication and Media studies, Computer Science and Information Systems, Pharmacy studies, Engineering (Civil and Structural), Accounting and Finance. Industry-based learning is at the heart of the educational experience, allowing students to gain practical experience as well as grow personally and professionally.

Name: RWTH Aachen University
About: RWTH Aachen University is among the leading European scientific and research institutions in Europe. More than 44,000 students are currently registered in 152 different courses of study, including more than 8,500 international students from 128 countries. Teaching at RWTH Aachen is first and foremost application-oriented. Its graduates are therefore sought-after as junior executives and leaders in business and industry. Teaching and Research at RWTH are characterized by an interdisciplinary approach and have relevance to real-world problems. RWTH Aachen University's success in Germany's Excellence Initiative reflects its outstanding reputation for research and education in science, technology, and engineering.

Name: Sabanci University
About: Sabanci University is a private educational institution founded by the Sabanci Group in July 1994. The Sabanci family, which is well-known in Turkey through a variety of businesses and community development projects, founded the university to create a "world university" that would produce Turkey's leaders in education and industry. When the University opened its doors in 1999, it became the first and only college in Turkey to offer a liberal arts undergraduate curriculum, with options of earning a degree in management or economics. Aside from the curriculum, the university has also received both applause and criticism for adopting a statement of academic freedom and hosting a small number of controversial faculty members. Today, SU is still a small and highly focused university with roughly 2,702 undergraduate students and 506 graduate students. Students enjoy the convenience of living on a state-of-the-art, self-sufficient campus that is only an hour away from the heart of Istanbul.

Name: Seoul National University
About: Seoul National University is a public research university located in Seoul, South Korea. It is one of the SKY universities and a part of the Flagship Korean National Universities. The university's main campus is located in Gwanak. The university comprises sixteen colleges, one graduate school and nine professional schools. SNU graduates dominate South Korea's academics, government, politics and business. QS World University Rankings (2024) ranked SNU as the 31th best university in the world and 7th in Asia.

Name: Shimane University
About: Shimane University was established as a national university in 1949. Shimane University’s goal is to enable students to develop international perspectives and their ability to be leaders in each region of the world. While studying there, students are equipped with the ability to cope with diverse problems like those they encounter in modern society. There are also empowered to take advantage of their accumulated knowledge, their cross-cultural awareness, and their technological skills. Furthermore, an important mission of Shimane University is to contribute to international society through creative research that is of an international standard.

Name: Singapore Management University
About: The Singapore Management University was founded in 2000. The campus, currently located outside the capital city in a fully refurbished facility in the heart of Singapore’s civic, cultural and business districts, offers state of the art technology, libraries and classroom facilities. SMU is modeled after the Wharton School of Business at the University of Pennsylvania, and its curriculum aims to groom outstanding business leaders and creative entrepreneurs capable of excelling in a rapidly changing and dynamic world. With exchange students from 47 institutions internationally, students will find themselves in a very diverse population and will have the advantage of a truly global experience.

Name: SKEMA Business School - Business
About: SKEMA strives to create an environment where students can learn in a diverse and multicultural atmosphere. The campus is located in Sophia Antipolis, approximately 25 miles southwest of Nice, in the European Silicon Valley. This ideal location provides students with exposure to the European, Latin and Mediterranean cultures and a perfect environment for enjoying beautiful weather and an abundance of travel opportunities in the French Riviera. SKEMA Business offers majors in International Business; Marketing; Finance; Hotel, Travel and Tourism Management; Sports Management, Management Information Systems and Management.

Name: Stockholm University
About: As one of the largest universities in Sweden, with over 64,000 undergraduate and master's students, Stockholm University offers unprecedented access to teaching and research  facilities. Stockholm  University, located in Sweden's capital city, is the region’s center for higher education and research in humanities, law, the natural and social sciences, and a focus for the work of leading international researchers. In the heart of Sweden's only national urban park, the University is surrounded by natural beauty, whilst being only a few minutes journey from the city center.

Name: TASSEP - Aarhus University
About: The Trans-Atlantic Science Student Exchange Program (TASSEP) is a consortium of member universities from the European Union, Canada and the United States. Through strong academic advising by science faculty, who work in close cooperation with their study abroad offices, TASSEP ensures that students are properly advised about course selection and eases the problems of receiving credit for courses taken abroad. The goal is to permit students to take most of their normal junior-level courses abroad and still be able to graduate on time. As an exchange program, TASSEP provides the most affordable means for students to study abroad by allowing students to pay their home university's tuition. As scientific activities, both in private industry as well as university and government laboratories, become increasingly international in scope, it is essential that science students become familiar with foreign cultures, languages, and economic systems. One of the most effective vehicles for addressing this problem is through exchange programs in which students spend time abroad, living much like the students at the foreign university. The goal of the present program is to facilitate these opportunities for science students. Science students face unique problems because of the large number of required courses in the standard four- or five-year curriculum, and because of the vertical structure of the science curriculum. There are 20 European member institutions of TASSEP and you can visit this website for more information on each.

Name: TASSEP - Friedrich Schiller Universität
About: The Trans-Atlantic Science Student Exchange Program (TASSEP) is a consortium of member universities from the European Union, Canada and the United States. Through strong academic advising by science faculty, who work in close cooperation with their study abroad offices, TASSEP ensures that students are properly advised about course selection and eases the problems of receiving credit for courses taken abroad. The goal is to permit students to take most of their normal junior-level courses abroad and still be able to graduate on time. As an exchange program, TASSEP provides the most affordable means for students to study abroad by allowing students to pay their home university's tuition. As scientific activities, both in private industry as well as university and government laboratories, become increasingly international in scope, it is essential that science students become familiar with foreign cultures, languages, and economic systems. One of the most effective vehicles for addressing this problem is through exchange programs in which students spend time abroad, living much like the students at the foreign university. The goal of the present program is to facilitate these opportunities for science students. Science students face unique problems because of the large number of required courses in the standard four- or five-year curriculum, and because of the vertical structure of the science curriculum. There are 20 European member institutions of TASSEP and you can visit this website for more information on each.

Name: Technical University of Denmark
About: The Technical University of Denmark, also known as DTU, is one of the world's leading Universities in technical and natural sciences. Founded in 1829 with the mission of creating value for the benefit of society, DTU is an international elite technical university where education, scientific advice, and innovation rest on a solid foundation of world-class research.

Name: Trinity College Dublin
About: The University of Florida’s College of Liberal Arts and Sciences offers students the opportunity to study at Trinity College Dublin. Located in a beautiful campus in the heart of Dublin’s city center, Trinity is Ireland’s highest ranked university according to the 2019 QS World University Ranking. It is home to 17,000 undergraduate and postgraduate students from 122 countries. The university promotes a diverse, interdisciplinary, inclusive environment which nurtures ground-breaking research, innovation, and creativity through engaging with issues of global significance. You can read the Study Abroad Guide for more information.

Name: UF in Aachen - Undergraduate Research
About: RWTH Aachen University is among Europe's leading scientific and research institutions. RWTH's Undergraduate Research Opportunities Program (UROP) is a summer program designed specifically for international students who wish to gain research experience in Germany. This 10-week program consists of both a research project at one of RWTH Aachen’s research institutes or labs, and an intensive German language course. Complimentary workshops are offered about intercultural learning, scientific methods, and research practice to prepare students for their research project. Each participating UF student is assigned a RWTH Aachen student as "buddy", who will mentor them and accompany them to various lesiure activities and excursions. You can learn more about the program here.

Name: UF in Australia - Fundamentals of Sport Performance
About: In Sydney, Australia, experience and take part in the sport and exercise culture of an iconic Australian city and former Olympic host city. Students earn 6 academic credits in this program. Undergraduate students will earn credit for APK3113C (Principles of Strength and Conditioning) and APK3163 (Sports Nutrition). Graduate students will earn credit for APK5177 (Strength and Conditioning for Beginning Practitioners) and APK6167 (Nutrition Aspects of Human Performance). APK undergraduate and graduate majors may use these courses towards their degree requirements; however, the program is open to all majors and will count as elective credits.

Name: UF in Belize - NGOs Sustainability and Development
About: The goal of this program is to provide knowledge on how Non-Governmental Organizations (nonprofits) are managed to promote social developments and environmental conservation around the globe. This program includes travels across Belize for field visits with 10 NGOs for a deeper understanding on their operations & impacts. Program assessments include case studies, field visit logs, discussions & presentations.

Name: UF in Berlin - MBA
About: This program is only open to approved MBA/graduate business students.

Name: UF in Berlin - Technology Innovation & Entrepreneurship
About: This program can be a life-changing experience to help you build and exercise technology innovation and entrepreneurship skills in one of the most dynamic and innovative cities in Europe.  Berlin is exploding as a European leader in technology innovation with 60% of all German investments in new ventures, especially tech startups, going to the over 500 Berlin startups a year.  UF in Berlin instructors and local entrepreneurs will guide students with instruction and connections to apply leading edge technology innovation models to building your own tech startups.  You’ll experience the challenges and excitement of cross-continent tech entrepreneurship while living in Europe’s “Fastest Growing Tech Hub” (Hubspot) and “Best Youth Destination” (TripSavvy).  Students who take both the UF in Berlin Innovation and Entrepreneurship courses offered back-to-back will also be two thirds of the way to completing the UF Engineering Innovation Certificate.

Name: UF in Brazil - MBA
About: This program is only open to approved MBA/graduate business students.

Name: UF in Brazil - MIB GIE
About: The Global Immersion Experience (GIE) course aims to give students an in-depth perspective of international business operations and their global challenges. Through hands-on involvement in solving actual business issues and engaging in site visits to diverse companies and institutions, coupled with academic lectures, students will develop a practical comprehension of the intricacies and practices in global business environments.

Name: UF in Brno - Engineering & Art
About: The UF in Brno program enables students to take a critical tracking class - PHY 2049—offered by Masaryk University (MU), the second largest university in Czech Republic, accompanied by a class on Engineering Art Sketchbook taught by a UF faculty. The goals are to introduce students to the importance of Science, Technology, Engineering, Arts, and Mathematics (STEAM) and explore the practice of art and engineering in Central Europe. Students will receive 3 transfer credits and 3 UF credits on the program.

Name: UF in Brussels - European Studies
About: Spend your summer learning about the European Union in the heart of Europe. Take advantage of an opportunity to partake fully in student life at Brussels School of Governance (BSOG), an English language international college within the Dutch-speaking Belgian Vrije Universiteit Brussel (VUB). Take courses with students from all over the world and benefit from all student resources (including full library, computer facilities, cafeteria, and gym access). This program is part of the European Union Studies Minor and Certificate program, as well as the International Studies major, but the program is open to all majors across all colleges.

Name: UF in Cannes - The Cannes Lions Experience
About: The UF CJC Cannes Lions study abroad programs offers undergraduate and graduate students a once-in-a-lifetime experience to meet and learn from the world’s top creative professionals. This interdisciplinary, 18-day program is located in the beautiful seaside city of Cannes, France. Students will learn about international creative thinking and storytelling from UF creative advertising and production professors, meet with production companies in the south of France, and immerse themselves in French language, landmarks, and culture. The final week culminates in attendance to the Cannes Lions International Festival of Creativity featuring the who’s who of the world’s advertising, PR, and production professionals, digital innovators, and marketers.

Name: UF in Cape Town - Software Engineering and UX Design Internship
About: UF in Cape Town Software Engineering and UX Design Internship program is a 6-credit curriculum and internship based on applying your knowledge and skills with experiential learning by working with local community organizations in Cape Town, South Africa. Students will have the chance to learn about the nature of computer science and global engineering as well as acquire practical skills in computer science innovation for social good. This is an opportunity of a lifetime. The program will integrate Computer Science Principles and the Software Engineering Agile Methodology to allow students to build innovative technologies to address real world problems. Students will work for 4 weeks with local community organizations and interact with leaders in top tech companies in South Africa. In order to determine the demands of the clients, design a cutting-edge technological product, create a prototype, and demonstrate the solution, the students will collaborate directly with the clients. As well, students will gain proficiency in computer science as well as communication to non-technical audiences. Students will also learn about South Africa through historical and cultural activities. They will learn to function and communicate successfully in multicultural situations, which is critical for their success throughout their internship and stay in South Africa. Students will return with not only professional skills, but also a greater understanding of another culture and an understanding of the function of engineering in a global, economic, environmental, and cultural context.

Name: UF in Chile - Viticulture and Wine in Chile
About: The primary goal of this program is to train students about current practices for establishing a vineyard and maintaining its health and productivity into the final quality of the grape. Students will learn about the cultural practices used in both grape production and winemaking, the importance of viticulture and wine sciences in the final quality of the wine, the grape varieties and their characteristics used in the production of wine, and the technology used in wine production. They will also learn the steps and equipment involved in basic winemaking as well as the importance of sensory evaluation of wines. Students will benefit from this experience by looking at and learning about vineyards and wineries in one of the well-known winegrape-growing countries.

Name: UF in Colombia - Global Health and Social Disparities
About: This program is designed to increase the student’s awareness and skills towards addressing global health and social disparities. Students will engage in lectures, discussion, and experiential activities (e.g., community events) to build the skills and knowledge necessary to be able to address both paradigms and build their given global perspective of the issues in the United States and Colombia. Students will have the opportunity to learn concepts and skills in the disciplines of public health, medicine, extension education and community development to understand how to evaluate and develop solutions in both countries. Students will be integrated into community-based events such as health fairs both in the United States and Colombia that will allow them to apply the concepts learned (e.g., assessing patient needs, intercultural communications to increase health literacy, understanding the role of culture in diagnoses and treatment, etc.) in the course to Latinos in need.

Name: UF in Costa Rica - CJC Explorers
About: UF in Costa Rica: CJC Explorers is an international environmental journalism experience for any majors who want to report on sustainable tourism spring semester with a week on the ground in Costa Rica March 15-22. We need writers, photographers, videographers, artists, web editors, campaign experts and YOU.

Name: UF in Costa Rica - Cultivating Community Through Service Learning
About: As part of this 6-credit program, students complete 45 hours of service work with various local organizations in San José, Costa Rica, such as museums, schools, health clinics, and community centers. Opportunities range from working in public schools and environmental parks to supporting healthcare in clinics, hospitals, and centers for people with disabilities. You will also enroll in a Spanish course focused on either language or Latin American culture.

Name: UF in Costa Rica - Plants and People in the Anthropocene
About: This program is approximately 4 weeks in duration with a short orientation session and activity in Gainesville before departure. While in Gainesville, students will be introduced to some of the research methodology and ecological concepts that they will further explore in Costa Rica. This program partners with the Organization for Tropical Studies (OTS) and the Tropical Agricultural Research and Higher Education Center (CATIE). The field based courses are led by UF instructors with support from local researchers and experts in different ecological zones in Costa Rica. Students will have the opportunity to conduct field research, analyze and present data. Students will travel to different regions of the country and have the opportunity to learn more about the local culture through course related ecological, historical and culture tours and workshops.

Name: UF in Costa Rica - Tropical Ecosystems
About: This program is an eight-day trip to Costa Rica during spring break to study ecotourism and recreation. You will learn about tropical ecosystems and environmentally based development in one of the most beautiful Latin American countries. This trip will include places in Costa Rica most tourists never see. You will learn about eco-tourism, cultural history, and the food production industry. The program is open to all UF students but specifically designed for students who have natural resource or agricultural-related majors.

Name: UF in Croatia - Clinical Shadowing
About: Shadow physicians in a hospital in Croatia for 20 hours per week in partnership with the Atlantis program. Students will rotate through multiple departments in the local hospital, observing physicians and residents in a variety of medical fields. The online internship course will allow students to reflect on their experiences. Each week students will also participate in a 1 day cultural excursion in the region, enjoying the beauty of Croatia and learning about Croatian culture.

Name: UF in Croatia - Food and Global Change
About: UF in Croatia: Food and Global Change provides students with a better understanding of the range of food production and subsistence, from small-scale and historical artisanal systems to modern larger-scale industrial systems. There is a focus on how global change, including climate change, invasive pests and pathogens, sociocultural and land-use change (e.g, urbanization) affect those systems, and the economic, social, and cultural consequences. Croatia (and the surrounding region of the Northern Balkans and Northern Adriatic Sea that includes Slovenia and eastern Italy) is an ideal location to explore this pressing global issue because it is a small country with highly diverse food systems that has recently entered the European Union.

Name: UF in Cusco - Experiential Learning for Health Professions
About: The Department of Spanish and Portuguese Studies and Department of Biology invite you to participate in an experience that will expand your linguistic and cultural fluency through language study and health-related community service. Based on Spanish-language level, students will be placed in a variety of settings, including hospitals, medical clinics, pharmacies and/or with dentists. On this program, students will have the opportunity to improve their command of Spanish, compare health systems, learn about diseases, and explore the cultures of South America. UF in Cusco is organized in conjunction with International Studies Abroad (ISA).

Name: UF in Czech Republic - MIB GIE
About: This Global Immersion Experience (GIE) is specifically for the Warrington College of Business's Masters of International Business (MIB) program. Only students who have been pre-selected are eligible to apply. The program will take place in Prague, Czech Republic from March 16-22, 2025. Students will earn 2 credits of GEB 6930 and pay logistical partner WorldStrides for all fees.

Name: UF in Dublin - AI Hackathon
About: This program offers a one-week experiential learning opportunity for students to participate in a hackathon in Ireland. During the event, students will collaborate with local university peers to create solutions focused on AI and sustainability. They will face the challenge of rapid development with an emphasis on global AI technology and gain experience in teamwork, collaboration, leadership, and innovation. They will have the chance to develop a software application that addresses AI for Social Good and contributes to global awareness and sustainable literacy by tackling one or more of the United Nations' Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs). UF students will learn about global AI, engineering, computer science, and design thinking from an international perspective. By applying software engineering methods in a hackathon setting, they will engage in hands-on learning, experiencing the fast-paced nature of technology development. The unique aspect of this program is the opportunity to work collaboratively with international students to develop AI technology that addresses global challenges.

Name: UF in Dublin - MBA
About: This program is only open to approved MBA/graduate business students.

Name: UF in Dublin - Study and Intern - CLAS
About: Spend a semester studying and working in Dublin, Europe’s Celtic Capital. Student's will study with both Irish and international students at Ireland’s University of Enterprise. Dublin City University is one of the best young universities in the world as evidenced by their consistent ranking in the Times Higher Education Top 100 under 50. They have a proud tradition of world-class academic excellence, research and innovation. This program brings the traditional semester abroad journey to the next level by providing students with academic, professional and personal exposure and experience in one of the world’s best study abroad locations.

Name: UF in Dublin - Study and Intern
About: Enjoy a beautiful country brimming with breathtaking scenery, music, and a rich and complex history. When will you have another opportunity to spend an entire semester in this fantastic location? The Warrington College of Business offers a study abroad program in Dublin that provides students a magnificent life experience - all while earning UF credits! Business and non-business courses are available. In addition, this program presents a unique opportunity for students to complete an international internship while studying in Dublin.

Name: UF in East Asia - Architecture
About: This is a 4-week traveling research studio/seminar that studies several East Asian megacities and landmark architectural projects, while offering the opportunity to speculate on future development strategies. The principal cities in question include Seoul, Tokyo, Kyoto, Osaka, and Singapore. Through the introduction of texts, case studies, and physically traveling to the aforementioned locations, students gain an understanding of the underlying forces driving and affecting urban development in the contemporary East Asian megacity. While these cities are in varying stages of historical development, each has gone through modernization and growth periods recently or is in the process of doing so, as well as going through boom/bust cycles. Some have past colonial influences, or is/was a former governmental seat of power. The principal questions posed through the course include: is there a distinctive form to urbanization in the region, or simply satisfying demands for rapid urban expansion through modernist principles and universally available building methods? What common problems, opportunities, and challenges faced that are particular to the region, and how might they differ from other parts of the world? The class will look at relevant social, political, and economic forces as well as forms of planning administration that shape and form the prevalent patterns of urbanization across a variety of scales including district, block, typology, and also traditional forms of settlement.

Name: UF in England - Disasters & Triumphs in British Engineering
About: The Industrial Revolution, which started in 19th century Britain, marks an era of unprecedented, sustained growth where many aspects of human life were fundamentally altered. Amongst these tides of change, some scholars believe, is nestled the birth of the Engineer. While people had been doing engineering work much earlier, the professionalization of innovation and design work during this time marked the emergence of Engineering as a profession of its own. This course aims to return to engineering “ground zero” to explore the development of engineering practices in England and allow students to examine engineering successes and failures from different eras of British history, while considering the legal, social, and ethical considerations that the engineers on those projects would have had to wrestle with. Site visits highlighting some of England’s engineering successes and failures, will provide the framework for conversations on the changes of the engineering discipline over time and the differences in how engineering is practiced outside of the United States. Furthermore, we will engage with the human centered nature of engineering through an exploration of the impact engineering success and failure has on the communities around them making it an excellent choice for both engineers as well as students interested in the ways these types of events can shape individuals, their communities, and society.

Name: UF in England - Inventors Nurses Farmers and Spies: The Curious History of Statistics
About: In the first part of this program, students will be introduced to the fascinating people who contributed to the historical beginnings of the fields of statistics and computing in England. Students will learn how the daughter of a notorious English poet came to write some of the first computer code, how a nurse during the Crimean War used data visualization to improve sanitary conditions in hospitals, how an afternoon tea party motivated a young statistician at an agricultural research station to codify the design of experiments, and how mathematicians and statisticians saved thousands of lives by breaking the Enigma code. In the second part of this program, students will be housed at Royal Holloway, University of London, and will conduct a research project inspired by these famous English statisticians. Students will work in teams using data available from our various program venues to analyze the data and to present their findings. Students may have the opportunity to collaborate with local experts.

Name: UF in Europe - Cities in Civilization
About: Cities are the engines of cultural creativity and technological innovation. This program will explore and seek to understand why and how cities continue to catalyze the growth of human civilization, from ancient Rome and the Italian Renaissance to modern culture and technologies. We travel by train through Europe, exploring the most important cities: London, Paris, Berlin, Vienna, Florence, and Rome. We start in London and finish in Rome five weeks later, with about five days in each of these historic cities Students in this program will experience the cultural and technological history of the role of cities, as well as learn to understand why and how cities continue to catalyze the growth of human civilization.

Name: UF in Europe - Ireland France & Italy
About: Enjoy experiencing multiple countries and cultures around Europe as you travel between Limerick, Ireland; Paris, France; and Rome, Italy. When will you have another opportunity to spend an entire semester in three different historic locations? The Warrington College of Business offers a study abroad program in Europe that provides students a magnificent life experience - all while earning UF credits! Business and non-business courses are available.

Name: UF in Europe - Sustainability Politics
About: This course is designed to immerse students in the complex interplay of political and cultural forces that shape sustainability practices across Europe. Through a blend of on-site learning, firsthand observation, and lectures, students will engage with the principles and practices of sustainability from a distinctly European perspective. The study abroad experience is central to the course, allowing students to explore the real-world application of sustainability policies across several key European destinations known for their innovative approaches to environmental challenges The countries of Switzerland and Germany are among the most advanced countries in the world in this regard (ranked 2nd, 4th respectively), having demonstrated a commitment and success in becoming sustainable. The world-famous eco-district Vauban, a “zero emissions” region of Freiburg, has been dubbed the most sustainable town on the globe. The curriculum takes full advantage of the European context, integrating experiential learning opportunities such as visits to iconic cities and landmark sites that showcase sustainable practices. These site visits and interactions provide students with an unparalleled chance to observe and study sustainability in action. By immersing themselves in this environment, students not only engage with the material academically but also see firsthand how different European societies integrate sustainability practices into their daily lives.

Name: UF in Florence - Global Perspectives
About: The UF in Florence program is offered in partnership with Florence University of the Arts (FUA). You can earn up to 6 credits of Italian language, Italian culture, or miscellaneous humanities in classes taught by UF and FUA faculty.

Name: UF in France - Science History Sustainability and Communication
About: Through this program, undergraduate students will learn about the rich history of science in France, examine current practical applications of sustainable science, explore cultural differences in science communications in the US and abroad, and build transferrable science communication skills. France provides a unique destination to highlight advances in science, technology, and mathematics. Pioneers from past millennia such as Pascal, Decarte, and Curie are now being joined by new changemakers who are tackling the challenges of today and forging a sustainable path forward. Our exploration will begin in Lyon, one of the oldest cities in France and the epicenter for the silk trade in Europe in the 15th century. After exploring these old-world processes, we will travel to Reims in the heart of the Champagne region to see sustainable science in action. The program will finish in Paris where we will learn about pigments and art, visit Europe’s oldest science and technology museum, and immerse ourselves in the culture of the City of Light. Students will have opportunities for professional development as they learn leadership and communication skills, grow academically, and become more aware of the international aspects of a career in science, thus marking their first step in joining the global scientific community.

Name: UF in Greece - Health Narratives & Problem Solving for Medical NGOs
About: This program examines healthcare and non-profit healthcare agencies in Greece. Students will engage with Greek residents via interviews, design challenges, and multimodal projects. Students will receive guest lectures from Greece’s leading experts in medicine and public health and shadow at local nonprofits. The Greek national health care system and economy provide important points of comparison for students familiar with the U.S. and will help students gain a richer understanding of the global diversity in health care systems and health care experiences. Experiential, international learning is important for all students with an interest in health and design, but especially for those who hope to pursue medical and medically related professions

Name: UF in Greece - Leadership for the Ages
About: Leadership has existed for ages – it’s time to experience it for yourself. During this immersive program, students will take two courses (6 credit-hours) that explore leadership in a global context through the lens of sustainable cities and communities (UN Sustainable Development Goal 11). The experience begins in northern Greece, travels through the Greek countryside, out to explore Greek islands, then ending in the birthplace of democracy – Athens. You will have the opportunity to explore UNESCO world heritage sites while learning about global leadership. Many visits will allow you to indulge in Greek foods and experience them from farm to table. Sustainability and agriculture will be at the forefront of our conversation as we explore all that Greek cities, communities, and islands have to offer.

Name: UF in Greece - One Health Education
About: One Health Education (OHE) is a transdisciplinary approach to deal with complex health issues through education and connection with the society. It follows the recognition of the interconnectedness of human health, animal health and the environment, which contributes to a holistic view of health. As global health and environmental issues are developing at an accelerated rate, there is a need to educate citizens so as to deal with the complexity of these issues and work for the protection of all species on earth. Students will be paired with undergrad and graduate students from University of Ioannina and George Mason University to create multi-cultural teams that will participate in a One Health Case competition held at the end of our study abroad experience. We will also include culture enrichment opportunities through touring local museums, visiting health systems in Greece, and exploring historical landmarks in Athens Greece.

Name: UF in Greece - Sustainability Exploration
About: This UF study abroad program in Greece offers a comprehensive, immersive experience in sustainability for undergraduate and international non-degree seeking students. It focuses on local best practices in various aspects of sustainability, including built environment and infrastructure. The program combines hands-on learning with intercultural experiences, allowing students to explore sustainability initiatives across Greek islands while engaging with local communities, organizations, and universities. By integrating Greek culture, language, and historical context, the program aims to foster a deep understanding of sustainability practices and their cultural significance, ultimately enhancing students’ global perspective and intercultural competence.

Name: UF in Hungary - African Migrations Today: Focus on Central Europe
About: While African migrations to Europe are both frequently in the international news and well-studied by academics, most of this attention focuses upon western European destinations. This program shifts that focus to central Europe where post-communist governments have adopted an often different set of stances or policies despite membership in the EU. UF students will interact with local university faculty, students, and various immigrant/minority populations in order to gain perspectives on African migration in Central Europe. The University of Pecs is the oldest university in Hungary and houses the one of the only Africa research centers in the CE region. Pecs is a former EU Capitol of Culture and also contains a UNESCO World Heritage site.

Name: UF in Iceland - Renewable Energy and Sustainability
About: The goal of the program is to understand and appreciate first-hand the sustainable renewable energy solutions in Iceland. Today, almost 100% of the electricity consumed in Iceland with a population of 368,000 people come from renewable energy sources. Students will learn about a wide range of renewable technologies such as geothermal energy, hydroelectric power, and energy policies in Iceland from experts in the fields. The program will include seminars from experts in energy sources and policies, tours of geothermal and hydroelectric power plants, and other visits to industries related to sustainability practices in Iceland.

Name: UF in Ireland - Internship & Global Culture
