Choose Manchester and you’ll put yourself ahead of the competition when the time comes to begin your career. With an award-winning careers service and courses built with your employability in mind, it’s no surprise that 94% of their graduates go straight into jobs or further study. If you’re interested in starting a business in the UK, the Masood Entrepreneurship Centre offers resources and support for student-led start-ups. The University of Manchester is part of the prestigious Russell Group of universities and their research and teaching quality is recognised across the globe. UM also prioritizes their international students, and will support you at all times while you’re there.

Name: University of Mannheim
About: UF's College of Liberal Arts and Sciences offers all UF students the opportunity to study at the University of Mannheim on exchange. Mannheim's renowned economic and social science programs are closely intertwined with humanities, law, mathematics, and computer science. The lecture halls are in close proximity to the city center, which is aligned symmetrically to the palace.

Name: University of Melbourne
About: The University of Florida’s College of Liberal Arts and Sciences offers students the opportunity to study in Melbourne, Australia. Founded in 1853, the University of Melbourne is consistently ranked one of the top two universities in Australia and within the top 50 in the world. The University is a leading research institution that has a truly global atmosphere with 27% of its student population coming from outside of Australia. The university is home to nearly 40,000 students and is located in the bustling business district of the city.

Name: University of Natural Resources and Life Sciences - Vienna (BOKU)
About: The University of Natural Resources and Life Sciences, Vienna – known also by the acronym "BOKU" – was initially founded as a university of agriculture and forestry in 1872. Today, it covers a unique scientific spectrum, ranging from agrarian issues to biotechnological research. Deriving from its mantra to be a "University of Life", BOKU aims to take on a special societal and political responsibility. Its core competency is the research and communication of potential sustainability solutions and the protection of natural resources. As a result, BOKU provides answers to issues of socio-political importance that affect us all. The University enjoys an outstanding reputation and has always been a place of encounter for different fields of science, research topics, opinions, attitudes, people and nationalities. Openness and diversity characterise everyday life at this university.

Name: University of New South Wales - Business
About: The University of New South Wales (UNSW) is a public university located in Kensington, Australia, approximately 4 miles south of Sydney’s central business district and 3 miles west of Bondi Beach. UNSW, established in 1949, is the founding member of the Group of Eight, a coalition of Australian research-intensive universities, and is ranked among the top 60 universities in the world. Visiting students will enjoy a modern campus within easy reach of Sydney’s commercial center and famous beaches, world class facilities and faculty, and unlimited opportunities to network and get involved with the UNSW’s 200 student organizations.  You can read the UNSW Exchange Guide for more information.

Name: University of New South Wales - CLAS
About: The University of New South Wales (UNSW) is a public university located in Kensington, Australia, approximately 4 miles south of Sydney’s central business district and 3 miles west of Bondi Beach. UNSW, established in 1949, is the founding member of the Group of Eight, a coalition of Australian research-intensive universities, and is ranked among the top 60 universities in the world. Visiting students will enjoy a modern campus within easy reach of Sydney’s commercial center and famous beaches, world class facilities and faculty, and unlimited opportunities to network and get involved with the UNSW’s 200 student organizations.  You can read the UNSW Exchange Guide for more information.

Name: University of New South Wales - Engineering
About: The University of New South Wales (UNSW) is a public university located in Kensington, Australia, approximately 4 miles south of Sydney’s central business district and 3 miles west of Bondi Beach. UNSW, established in 1949, is the founding member of the Group of Eight, a coalition of Australian research-intensive universities, and is ranked among the top 60 universities in the world. Visiting students will enjoy a modern campus within easy reach of Sydney’s commercial center and famous beaches, world class facilities and faculty, and unlimited opportunities to network and get involved with the UNSW’s 200 student organizations.  You can read the UNSW Exchange Guide for more information.

Name: University of Sydney
About: The University of Florida’s College of Liberal Arts and Sciences offers students the opportunity to study in Sydney, Australia. Founded in 1850, the University of Sydney is Australia’s oldest university. Not only is the University of Sydney one of the country’s most prestigious universities, but it is also one of the world’s most comprehensive research and teaching institutions and offers a broad range of academic subjects for students to study. The historic campus is located near the Central Business District and is easily accessible to downtown Sydney.

Name: University of Warsaw
About: University of Warsaw, established in 1816, is Poland's largest and finest university. It plays a major role in the intellectual, political, and cultural life of Poland, and has been recognized throughout the world as a leading academic centre in this part of Europe. Approximately 45,000 students attend the University of Warsaw, including around 5,000 international students each year. Click here to visit UW's webpage for exchange students.

Name: Utrecht University
About: The Netherlands is a small country in the northwest of Europe. While famous for windmills, cheese, world-renowned artists like Van Gogh and Rembrandt, the Netherlands has much more to offer students in terms of culture, art, history, and memorable experiences. Utrecht is the 4th-largest city in the Netherlands, and is very much an international student town. Utrecht University is the Netherlands' top university, and one of the most prestigious institutions in the world. It's campus is split between Utrecht's city center (downtown) and the 'Science Park', where some classroom and residential buildings are located. As a UF student, you are able to apply for exchange at either the main Utrecht University campus or University College Utrecht (UCU), the international liberal arts honors college of Utrecht University, which has its own campus. For more information on UCU, visit our website here.

Name: Waseda University
About: Waseda consistently ranks among the most academically selective and prestigious universities in Japanese university rankings.It is organized into 36 departments: 13 undergraduate schools and 23 graduate schools. On Waseda University’s 30th anniversary in October 1913, President Shigenobu Okuma proclaimed its newly adopted Mission Statement. Waseda University holds as its founding principles the preservation of the independence of scholarship, the promotion of the practical application of scholarship, and the fostering of good citizens. For more information please refer to: Center for International Education Waseda University Handbook Waseda University Fact Sheet 2023

Name: Western Sydney University
About: Western Sydney University was founded in 1989, with a contemporary approach to study, work and innovation. They combine academic study with practical experience to deliver useful courses to help drive you towards your career goals. The university has six campuses located in the Greater Western Sydney (GWS) region. GWS is a center for trade with the third largest economy in Australia. More than 150 of the nation's top 500 companies are located in GWS. The campuses of the Western Sydney University are all connected to the local community in order to continue to grow and develop with GWS.

Name: WHU - Otto Beisheim School of Management
About: WHU – Otto Beisheim School of Management is an internationally oriented and privately financed business school. Since its establishment in 1984, WHU has proved itself a paragon of future-oriented research and teaching in business administration. WHU currently hosts approximately 1,400 students and has an international network that includes 200 partner universities all over the world. The school is AACSB, EQUIS and FIBBA accredited. WHU aims to achieve 4 things with its students: Practical orientation, internationality, personality development and technological orientation. With a focus on these 4 things, and helped by the small size of the university, WHU students are among the best in Europe and the faculty is open to helping students outside the classroom. Many industry professionals are also invited to WHU to teach courses with a practical approach. Learn more about this program on the Heavener International Programs website.

Name: WU - Vienna University of Economics and Business - Graduate Level
About: WU is the EU’s largest educational institution for business and economics, business law, and social sciences, with about 26,000 students. It was founded in 1898 as the “Imperial Export Academy,” with a curriculum designed to prepare students for employment in international trade. In 1975, the name changed to what it is today, and the university experienced significant growth between 1981 and 1993. WU strongly values international education and research-based teaching, and maintains EQUIS accreditation for quality control. The university recently remodeled and the new campus includes new buildings and more open green space. Learn more about this program on the Heavener International Programs website.

Name: WU - Vienna University of Economics and Business - Undergraduate Level
About: WU is the EU’s largest educational institution for business and economics, business law, and social sciences, with about 26,000 students. It was founded in 1898 as the “Imperial Export Academy,” with a curriculum designed to prepare students for employment in international trade. In 1975, the name changed to what it is today, and the university experienced significant growth between 1981 and 1993. WU strongly values international education and research-based teaching, and maintains EQUIS accreditation for quality control. The university recently remodeled and the new campus includes new buildings and more open green space. Learn more about this program on the Heavener International Programs website.

Name: Yonsei University
About: Founded in 1885, Yonsei University is the oldest private university in Korea, as well as Korea’s most internationalized and liberal institution of higher learning. Yonsei University is Asia’s highest ranked private university and is ranked 73rd in the world by The World University Rankings 2023. Yonsei is home to over 37,000 undergraduate and postgraduate students. The university maintains an extensive international network with over 700 partner institutions in 77 countries and educates the largest number of international students among Korean universities, with over 6,000 in 2022.

About: There are many study abroad programs available through third-party providers, foreign institutions, and other U.S. universities. These are referred to as "Non-UF Programs." To learn more about them, please visit our website. This page displays a selection of some of the more popular Non-UF program options available to you. However, please note this is not a comprehensive list. If you find a program that is not listed here, you still may be able to participate.

Name: SRAS - Russian as a Second Language (Tbilisi)
About: Semester at Sea ("SAS") is a multi-destination non-UF study abroad program. During this program, students live on a ship for an entire Fall or Spring semester and sail around the world to visit between 9-12 countries. This program is open to students of all majors from all over the world (although mainly U.S. students). It is accredited through Colorado State University.
